confirmation.guidance.p3 = Your employer will use this information to assess your eligibility for Statutory Paternity Pay (SPP) and/or paternity leave. If your request is approved, you will receive your SPP from your employer.
confirmation.guidance.p4 = If you are not eligible, your employer must tell you within 28 days if you do not qualify and why using form SPP1. If you are not entitled to SPP you may be entitled to other government help. Contact any Jobcentre Plus office for further information.
confirmation.guidance.p5.1 = If you disagree with your employer’s decision you can contact the
confirmation.guidance.p5.link1.text = Statutory Payments Dispute Team
confirmation.guidance.p5.link1.href = https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/hm-revenue-customs/contact/statutory-payment-dispute-team
confirmation.guidance.p5.2 = You must do this within 6 months of the day you were notified of your employer’s decision.
